It's been pretty painful figuring this stuff out. A lot of the time I feel like I'm nothing without making & posting art, while also being held back by own disabilities. It's not healthy.

I remember when I was younger, I really wanted to be one of those online artists that people watched grow into someone successful since their early adult days because I craved that kind of support from my father. However, my undiagnosed ADHD prevented me from drawing frequently.

I think I'm also sad since I just saw my dad today after a couple months. We had a good conversation and everything. But he was never there for me growing up and these daddy issues have manifested into my need for a lot of online engagement.

I'm thankful I have it now, but I feel like I missed out on living up to some sort of potential in my childhood because I was too afraid to try or too distracted and stuck to get things done.
